# OpenPose (infrastructure)

The engine-owned OpenPose pose resource and the canonical hint rasterizer. Not an ECS system — used by
DiffusionSystem to build a ControlNet Control Hint, and loaded by ResourceManagerSystem (ADR 0008).

## OpenPoseSkeleton
A pregenerated pose resource: the COCO-18 (OpenPose BODY_18) keypoints of a single fixed pose plus the
canvas they were authored against. Holds only joint positions + per-joint confidence — not an image.
Loaded from the OpenPose JSON export format (`Create`/`CreateFromJsonString`): a top-level array whose
first element carries `people[].pose_keypoints_2d` (flat `[x, y, confidence]` triples in COCO-18 order)
and `canvas_width`/`canvas_height`. Missing keypoints stay at confidence 0; malformed JSON yields null.

## RasterizeOpenPoseHint
Renders the canonical OpenPose skeleton into an RGB `pg::Image`: a black background with each of the 17
BODY-18 limbs drawn as a coloured stick and each of the 18 joints as a coloured disc, using the standard
OpenPose palette keyed to the COCO-18 joint order. Joints with confidence <= 0 are skipped, as is any
limb touching one. Keypoints are supplied in the output image's pixel space. Limb sticks are solid (a
faithful-enough approximation of OpenPose's alpha-blended polygons for ControlNet conditioning).

## TransformKeypoints / MakeCanvasToImageTransform
`MakeCanvasToImageTransform` builds the glm::mat3 mapping a skeleton's canvas-space keypoints onto an
output image of a given pixel size; `TransformKeypoints` applies any homogeneous 2D transform (the
canvas mapping composed with the request's Skeleton Transform) to every keypoint before rasterization.
The engine owns the OpenPose convention; it never detects pose from a photo.
